# values.sops.env — sops-encrypted secrets for this app.
#
# This file is committed as plaintext on bootstrap, but the *next* edit
# MUST encrypt it before the commit lands:
#
#   sops --encrypt --in-place values.sops.env
#
# The `.sops.yaml` config in this repo points the encryption rule at MeKo's
# Azure Key Vault — you need `az login` (or another Azure auth path) before
# sops can encrypt or decrypt.
#
# Per-stage convention:
#   values.sops.env              — base, used by every stage (dev vault)
#   values.staging.sops.env      — staging-only, encrypted with staging vault
#   values.prod.sops.env         — prod-only, encrypted with prod vault
#
# Format: KEY=value, one per line. Comments start with `#`. Sops encrypts
# the values but leaves the keys readable so you can grep for secret names.
#
# Example (BEFORE encryption):
#   STRIPE_API_KEY=sk_live_REPLACE_ME
#   DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host:5432/db
